ch.iserver.ace.collaboration
Interface Session

All Known Subinterfaces:
ConfigurableSession, PublishedSession
All Known Implementing Classes:
PublishedSessionImpl, SessionImpl
public interface Session

A session represents one particular editing session of a shared document. An implementation of this class allows communicating with the other participants in the session. This includes sending/receiving of requests as well as sending/receiving of awareness information.

A session is obtained either by joining a published document or by accepting an invitation of another user.

Method Detail

lock

void lock()
Locks the session's logic so that only the calling thread can access the concurrency sensitive parts of the logic. This method must be called before any send call is invoked.

Throws:
InterruptedRuntimeException

unlock

void unlock()
Unlocks the session's logic so that other threads may gain access to the session's logic (the operational transformation engine). Take care that every call to lock() is accompanied by a exactly one call to this method.

getParticipantId

int getParticipantId()
Gets the participant id of the local user. This id uniquely identifies the user within an editing session. The participant id is available to the application mainly for informational purposes. The Session implementation will know when and how to use this id appropriately, without intervention of the application layer.

Returns:
the participant id of the local user

leave

void leave()
Leaves the session. After calling this method, the session becomes stale, i.e. it should not be used anymore.

getParticipant

Participant getParticipant(int participantId)
Gets the participant with the given id. If there is no participant with the given id in the session, null is returned.

Parameters:
participantId - the participant id of the participant to retrieve
Returns:
the Participant with the given id or null if there is none
